==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dense
<hw>Dense</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>densus</ets>;
akin to Gr. <grk>dasy`</grk> thick with hair or leaves: cf. F.
<ets>dense</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the constituent parts
massed or crowded together; close; compact; thick; containing much
matter in a small space; heavy; opaque; <as>as, a <ex>dense</ex> crowd;
a <ex>dense</ex> forest; a <ex>dense</ex> fog.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All sorts of bodies, firm and fluid, <qex>dense</qex> and
rare.</q> <rj><qau>Ray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To replace the cloudy barrier <qex>dense</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Stupid; gross; crass; <as>as, <ex>dense</ex>
ignorance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Densely</ent>⟦br⟧
